" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 537px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Infant asymmetrical tonic neck reflex",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 517px; height: 423px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Asymmetrical tonic neck reflex is characterized by extension of the upper and lower extremities on the side to which the head and neck is turned with flexion of the contralateral upper extremity (fencing posture). It appears beginning at 35 weeks gestation, is well-established by one month of age, and disappears by three to&nbsp;four months of age in a term infant.",
